	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=68530><span id= >neuroshock</span></a><br><span id=notbold>10 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I love this idol!<br><br>SUPER stats for a Rogue of Bristlebane.&nbsp;&nbsp;I wish all idols were this useful. Unlike every other idol I sell NOBODY balks at the price paid for this idol.  To the contrary, most people when they find out they have to be a follower of Bristlebane to equip it curse openly.  It is a shame that prolly half of all rogues are not followers of Bristlebane.  No other idol fits a rogue so well!<br><br>Strangely I get offers of trades on this item more than any other idol.  For some reason rogues seem to have a vast quantity of tradeable goods...and I've accepted a few that were just DANG fine trades for both me and the buyer.  In retrospect it might be because they wanted to procure it immediately and werent carrying that much cash...I dunno. *shrug*<br><br>All I can say is that like all the others its hatefully hard to make, but unlike most others it actually sells easily. Dex/Agility in a Ranged Slot item is just pure heaven.<br><br>This idol would ALMOST have made it worth becoming a 188+ potter, but there simply aren't enough rogues to sell a decent quantity to that follow Bristlebane.<br><br>So...for now I'll just have to listen to most ppl curse because they chose the wrong god!<br><br>Congrats to anyone who can actually equip this thing!  If your looking for one I try to keep one on hand or the materials to make one.  Send a tell or email me.<br><br>Be Safe,<br>Trafalgar<br>26th Cleric of Tunare   Drinal</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Trafalgar<br>neuroshock@bigfoot.com<br>(NeuroShock)</td></tr>
